Package: BioSeqAligner
Type: Package
Title: A DNA sequence alignment, visualization and manipulation tool
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Kashvi Shah
Maintainer: <kashvishah4@gmail.com>
Description: A collection of tools for biological sequence analysis and
    alignment. Alongside sequence manipulation helpers (motif finding, reverse
    complement, transcription, GC content, k-mers, codon usage), the package
    provides true pairwise alignment (Needleman-Wunsch and Smith-Waterman with
    affine gaps) for DNA, RNA, and protein; progressive multiple sequence
    alignment; alignment-quality metrics; FASTA/FASTQ I/O; batch (mini-BLAST)
    search; colour-coded alignment and dot-plot visualization; neighbour-joining
    trees; primer design via Primer3 with built-in specificity screening;
    sequence-based CpG island detection with a curated (non-computed) lookup
    of well-established gene-disease methylation associations; and an
    interactive Shiny app. It aims to gather in one package the common tasks
    that otherwise require juggling several bioinformatics tools.
